{"title":"Luma Cycles Starparty Adventure Gravel Bike","link":"https://theradavist.com/luma-cycles-starparty-adventure-gravel-bike/","date":1741877774000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_02.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_02.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>Luma Cycles is a brand based in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, specializing in adventure bike platforms. Its suspension-corrected titanium chassis Starparty is a <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/adventure-gravel-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">adventure gravel bike</a> engineered to work with a 60mm suspension fork and 50 mm tires…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Luma Starparty Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frame: LūMA Cycles Grade 9 3Al/2.5V Titanium Double-Butted</li>\n<li>Headset: Upper ZS44/28.6 Lower EC44/40</li>\n<li>Seat Tube Diameter: 31.6 mm</li>\n<li>Bottom Bracket: T47-68</li>\n<li>Hanger: UDH</li>\n<li>Axle: 12×142 Thru-axle</li>\n<li>Front Derailleur Mount: 34.9 mm band-clamp</li>\n<li>Brake Mount: Flat Mount 160 mm</li>\n<li>Max Tire: 700×50 mm</li>\n<li>Max Chainring: 1x: 42T 2x: 50/34T</li>\n<li>Mounts: 3 bottles, top tube, rack, fenders, fork legs</li>\n<li>Max Rider Weight: 250lbs</li>\n<li>Country of Manufacture: China</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_03.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_03.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_03.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_Geo.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_Geo.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>With a high stack and a more snappy geometry than a drop-bar-29er, the Luma Starparty will ride quickly and responsive, navigating swoopy singletrack and double track forest roads with ease.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_04.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_04.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_04.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_04.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_05.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_05.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_05.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_05.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_06.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_06.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_06.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_06.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Frame Details</h3>\n<p>Luma Cycles’ Chinese factory partners have meticulously crafted each frame with details including a UDH hanger and internal routing ports through the chainstay yoke.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_07.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_07.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_07.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/03/Luma_Cycles_Starparty_Gravel_07.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The Starparty is available through Luma Cycles direct as a frameset or various build kits. While these first frames are made in China, the brand mentioned offering custom US-made models coming down the road. Check out more at <a href=\"https://lumacycles.com/products/starparty\" target=\"_blank\">Luma Cycles</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/luma-cycles-starparty-adventure-gravel-bike/\">Luma Cycles Starparty Adventure Gravel Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"61b50c69082e5643b91992a6b690ab34ccb34575b4c4ed12f4d2f28ba688fb22","category":"Cycling"}